# Round Flow & States

A round in OpenEdge 14 goes through several states managed by the GameTicker system.

## Round States


PreRoundLobby  -> Players wait in lobby, select characters
InRound        -> Active gameplay
PostRound      -> Round over, results shown


## State Transitions

- [bold]PreRoundLobby -> InRound:[/bold] When enough players ready up, or admin forces start
- [bold]InRound -> PostRound:[/bold] When win/lose condition triggers, or admin ends round
- [bold]PostRound -> PreRoundLobby:[/bold] After delay, server resets

## Listening to Round Events

Systems can react to round state changes:


private void OnRoundStart(RoundStartedEvent args)
{
    // Initialize systems for new round
}

private void OnRoundEnd(RoundEndedEvent args)
{
    // Clean up, calculate results
}


